Description: systemd-managed Jool instances inside dedicated network namespaces
 jool-netns wraps Jool NAT64 or SIIT instances in dedicated network namespaces.
 It creates a namespace and veth pair, loads a standard Jool JSON config, and
 can optionally install host-side routes and masquerade rules for the namespace.
